terms.title: Entitlement
terms.Text: The belief that one is inherently deserving of privileges or special treatment

terms.title: Extrinsic Motivation
terms.Text: The type of motivation that occurs when the inclination to pursue and persist is imposed by positive external factors (i.e. scholarships, trophies) or negative external factors (i.e. threat of punishment, coercion).

terms.title: Intrinsic Motivation
terms.Text: The type of motivation that occurs when the inclination to pursue and persist is driven by an interest or enjoyment of the task itself, and exists within the individual rather than relying on external pressure.

terms.title: Motivation
terms.Text: The inclination to pursue and persist in the journey towards a desired outcome.
